step_data.thought: I've successfully clicked on the 'Layers' button, which should have opened the map layers panel. Looking at the accessibility tree, I can see that there are different map layer options available in a list (items 231, 249, 267, 285) corresponding to different map styles: 'Standard', 'CyclOSM', 'ÖPNVKarte', and 'Humanitarian'. Before I start switching between these layers, I need to navigate to Central Park specifically. Since I'm already in New York, I should search for 'Central Park' to focus the map on that area. I'll use the search box (bid 145) to do this.
